UID:-RwHIrJHR1lW9Bxk0YjfB
SUMMARY:SP 202: Fabric Printing PILOT *MEMBERS ONLY*
DTSTAMP:20260405T193004Z
DTSTART:20260411T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:This class is only available for VERA members. If you are looki
	ng to sign up for SP 202: Fabric Printing\, there is another class availab
	le for sign up on June 13th!\n\nDo you dream of people wearing your artwor
	k out on the streets? Want to make shirts for your friend’s music project?
	 Level up your fabric printing experience and take home your own printed t
	ote bag in this 3-hour intermediate-level fabric printing class! In this h
	ands-on workshop\, you’ll explore the use-cases for printing on fabric\, p
	ractice properly setting up on the t-shirt press\, and registering a 2-col
	or fabric print. Students will receive three shirts to print on (sizes S—3
	XL are available). Students will be printing a Vera specific design\, excl
	usive to the 202 class.\n\nStudents must complete Screenprint 101 before a
	ttending this class.\n\nhttps://link.dice.fm/L3b0e578a8c6\n\nFrom The Vera
	 Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/L3b0e578a8c6
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:vera-project
CATEGORIES:The Vera Project
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
